1. cs.CV (Computer Vision): The paper deals with camera pose estimation using real-time camera data, which is a core problem in computer vision. 
2. cs.RO (Robotics): Camera pose estimation is a crucial component in robotics, especially in tasks such as robot navigation and mapping. 
3. cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper proposes a novel partitioning scheme and motion averaging technique, which involve machine learning concepts such as clustering and optimization. 
4. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The proposed approach involves dynamic initialization and self-adaptive optimization, which are AI techniques. 
5. cs.GR (Graphics): Camera pose estimation is also relevant in computer graphics applications such as virtual reality and augmented reality.
